methods.describeDifferences:
Enumerate the differences between this ColumnDefinition, and another one.
 Lines will be of the form "lhs attribute 'value' does not match rhs attribute 'value'.

:param differences: (java.util.List<java.lang.String>) - an array to which differences can be added
:param other: (io.deephaven.db.tables.ColumnDefinition) - the ColumnDefinition under comparison
:param lhs: (java.lang.String) - what to call "this" definition
:param rhs: (java.lang.String) - what to call the other definition
:param prefix: (java.lang.String) - begin each difference with this string
methods.getObjectCodecType:
Get the appropriate ObjectCodecType for this column definition.

:return: (io.deephaven.db.tables.ColumnDefinition.ObjectCodecType) The StandardObjectCodec, or null if none is appropriate
methods.isCompatible:
Compares two ColumnDefinitions somewhat more permissively than equals, disregarding matters of
 storage and derivation.

:param other: (io.deephaven.db.tables.ColumnDefinition) - - The ColumnDefinition to compare to.
:return: (boolean) True if the ColumnDefinition defines a column whose data is compatible with this ColumnDefinition.
